DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, April 14\, 2026\, 11am - 3pm\n\nTrained volunteers wi
	ll be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\n\nL
	ocation Link:\n\nBallard Branch\n\nRoom Location: Meeting Room\n\nRegistra
	tion Required: Registration is not required.\n\nDetailed Description: This
	 service is free and available to individuals only. The free service is no
	t available for business tax returns. To receive tax help\, bring the foll
	owing documents:\,\n\nRequired:\n\nPhoto identification\, Social Security 
	cards or Individual Taxpayer Identification Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyon
	e listed on the tax return.\, Proof of income\, for example\, W2s and 1099
	s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Official documents on Social Security A
	dministration letterhead\, Medicare card \\(if Social Security number is f
	ollowed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to provide information about health car
	e coverage for each person on the return.\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year's
	 tax return\, if available\, Bank account and routing numbers for direct d
	eposit of refunds\, Photocopies or computer print-outs of any of these doc
	uments will be accepted.Original documents highly recommended.\, Due to fe
	deral budget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain ta
	x forms and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at
	\n\nwww.irs.gov .\, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms 
	from Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nA
	ARP .\n\nEvent Logistics: AARP Tax Help locations serve anyone who earned 
	less than $80\,000 in 2025.\, For eligibility details\, contact AARP at 88
	8-227-7669.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,\n\nAsk
	 Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide accommo
	dations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\ncontactL
	EAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodations.\, A
	ll Library programs are free and open to the public.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6
	amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-04-14T00
