SUMMARY:Free Tax Help
DTSTAMP:20260413T004129Z
DTSTART:20260414T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Tuesday\, April 14\, 2026\, 12:30 - 6:30pm\n\nTrained volunteer
	s will be available to answer questions and prepare personal tax returns.\
	n\nLocation Link:\n\nCentral Library\n\nRoom Location: Level 5 - Mixing Ch
	amber Meeting Room\n\nRegistration Required: Registration is not required.
	\n\nDetailed Description: Drop-in tax help is offered on a first-come\, fi
	rst-served basis.\, This service is free and available to individuals only
	.\, The free service is not available for business tax returns.\, To recei
	ve tax help\, bring the following documents:\,\n\nRequired Documents:\n\nP
	hoto identification\, Social Security cards or Individual Taxpayer Identif
	ication Numbers \\(ITIN\\) for everyone listed on the tax return\, Proof o
	f income\, for example\, W2s and 1099s \\(Social Security benefits\\)\, Of
	ficial documents on Social Security Administration letterhead\, Medicare c
	ard \\(if Social Security number is followed by an "A"\\)\, Be prepared to
	 provide information about health care coverage for each person on the ret
	urn\,\n\nRecommended:\n\nLast year's tax return\, if available\, Bank acco
	unt and routing numbers for direct deposit of refunds\, Photocopies or com
	puter print-outs of any of these documents will be accepted.\, Due to fede
	ral budget cuts the IRS is unable to provide the Library with certain tax 
	forms and instruction booklets.\, Most IRS forms are available online at\n
	\nwww.irs.gov. \, You may make free black-and-white prints of the forms fr
	om Library computers:\n\nwww.spl.org/Print \, Thanks to our partner\n\nUni
	ted Way of King County .\n\nEvent Logistics: United Way Tax Help locations
	 serve anyone who earned less than $80\,000 in 2025 \\(or less than $96\,0
	00 for non-single filers\\).\, For eligibility details\, contact United Wa
	y at 206-461-3700.\n\nContact Us: If you have questions about this event\,
	\n\nAsk Us\n\nor call 206-386-4636.\n\nADA Accommodations: We can provide 
	accommodations for people with disabilities at Library events. Please\n\nc
	ontactLEAP\n\nat least seven days before the event to request accommodatio
	ns.\, All Library programs are free and open to the public.\,\n\nhttps://s
	eatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/free-tax-help/18162991/2026-04-14T00
