BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:NPUvR65pT7guJT7U2gU0A
SUMMARY:Type Design Basics
DTSTAMP:20260413T004129Z
DTSTART:20260422T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Class Overview\n\nSo you want to design a typeface? Learn how t
	o hand-draw letters and digitize them to create your own unique functional
	 font! In this practical workshop\, students will create an original text 
	typeface based on traditional European calligraphy. Whether you want to de
	velop your typography skills\, improve your lettering practice\, or become
	 a type designer\, learning the fundamentals of type design can bring your
	 skills to the next level.\n\nExplore both analog media \\(pen on paper\\)
	 and digital media \\(computer\\). Learn how to use a calligraphy pen to d
	evelop an understanding of the underlying structure of the Latin alphabet.
	 Then you can work on improving your drawings digitally\, and create a typ
	eface using Glyphs \\(or the font editor of your choice\\).  \n\nClass tim
	e is dedicated to working on your project with individualized feedback\, s
	upplemented by lectures\, technical demonstrations\, and group critique. B
	y the end of the class\, you will have a working text typeface of your own
	 creation\, as well as a sketch-to-screen workflow that you can use for fu
	ture font creation.\n\nStudents will be encouraged to spend up to 10 hours
	 on homework outside of class time. Designing a typeface is a laborious pr
	ocess\, but time flies when experimenting\, drawing\, and editing!\n\nThis
	 class is offered in partnership with the amazing Seattle Creative Academy
	 \\(but this class is not part of their program and is not for credit/degr
	ee\\)! See also: Experimental Lettering and other Graphic Design or art cl
	asses on our website.\n\nLearning Objectives\n\nLearn the basics of callig
	raphy\n\nUnderstand the structure and patterning of the Latin alphabet\n\n
	Create your own original letterforms\n\nDigitize and refine your original 
	design\n\nLearn how to optimize a typeface for text\n\nBecome familiar wit
	h a sketch-to-screen digital type design workflow\n\nWho Might Enjoy This 
	Class?\n\nAnyone who wants to develop their own custom font\n\nGraphic des
	igners\, illustrators\, lettering artists\, type designers -- anyone with 
	related experience who would like to hone their type design skills\n\nArch
	itects\, engineers\, artists\, crafters\, writers\, book lovers -- anyone 
	interested in the form of letters who would enjoy creating and using their
	 own handmade font\n\nNo prerequisites\, but basic graphic design/typograp
	hy knowledge is recommended\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/detai
	ls/type-design-basics/18345520/2026-04-21T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/type-design-basics/183455
	20/2026-04-21T00
LOCATION:Seattle Central College Continuing Education\, 1701 Broadway\, Sea
	ttle\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:kRQbjl6a5vyFllupiwmdI
SUMMARY:Make a difference for cats and dogs in need!
DTSTAMP:20260413T004130Z
DTSTART:20260422T070000Z
DESCRIPTION:Are you interested in using your time\, talent\, and energy to 
	support the vision of a healthy and happy home for every cat and dog in Wa
	shington?\n\nIf yes\, then please consider joining our Board!\n\nPawsitive
	 Alliance\, a volunteer driven tax-exempt nonprofit organization\, is havi
	ng an open call for Board Members. Founded in 2005\, the mission of Pawsit
	ive Alliance is to help end the euthanasia of adoptable dogs and cats in W
	ashington by increasing adoptions\, supporting spay and neuter programs\, 
	and improving pet retention.\n\nPawsitive Alliance advances are mission th
	rough our three programs:\n\n-  Adoption program: \\#WhyNotMePets campaign
	\, highlighting long-term homeless pets\, and supporting adoption events t
	o help homeless finds homes\n\n-  Spay/Neuter: providing vouchers and fina
	ncial and logistical support to increase surgeries and access to end pet o
	verpopulation and suffering\n\n-  Pet retention: collecting and distributi
	ng pet food and supplies and offering pet ID tags and microchips to keep p
	ets thriving with their caretakers\n\nOur programs and activities prioriti
	ze increasing services for pets\, people\, and places across Washington st
	ate with few resources.\n\nPawsitive Alliance’s biggest strengths are mark
	eting\, organizing\, fundraising\, and collaborating.  We work with more t
	han 50 human and animal-welfare partners each year. Since 2005\, we have h
	elped over 8\,000 animals find homes\, delivered over 170\,000 pounds of d
	onated pet food\, and facilitated more than 11\,000 spay and neuter surger
	ies.\n\nThe Pawsitive Alliance Board is a hands-on group of committed indi
	viduals\, investing their time and resources to support our mission.  As w
	e celebrate our 20th anniversary in 2025\, and look to the future\, we are
	 looking to add individuals from diverse backgrounds to join the Board and
	 help the organization’s continued success and growth.  Ideal candidates a
	re committed to our mission\, can commit at least 10-15 per month to the o
	rganization\, are able to represent the organization in the community\, ar
	e ready to engage in strategy setting\, fundraising and networking\, and b
	ring a well-rounded set of skills to a unique and hard-working team.​\n\nP
	awsitive Alliance is always interested in bringing greater diversity and n
	ew areas of expertise\, energy\, and skills to the Board. For more informa
	tion on the organization\, refer to our website at www.pawsitivealliance.o
	rg.  Please fill out our Board Application if you share our passion for he
	lping to end pet homelessness in Washington and are interested in serving 
	and helping end pet overpopulation.\n\nThose interested in applying should
	 email our Board Recruitment Committee at info@pawsitivealliance.org.\n\nh
	ttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cats-an
	d-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-04-22T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/make-a-difference-for-cat
	s-and-dogs-in-need/17259552/2026-04-22T00
LOCATION:Pawsitive Alliance\, 14150 NE 20th St. F1-233\, Bellevue\, WA
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:JUknzRtmb9RCGluEcOJrw
SUMMARY:Bartender's Circle Summit 2026 - Seattle Cocktail Week
DTSTAMP:20260413T004130Z
DTSTART:20260422T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:The world’s bar community is converging on Seattle. For three d
	ays\, we are transforming the iconic Pacific Place into a multi-floor glob
	al campus for the hospitality elite. This isn’t just a regional seminar—it
	’s where the industry meets to define the next era of cocktail culture.Whe
	ther you are traveling from across the ocean or across the city\, the Summ
	it offers a masterclass in professional evolution\, led by the most influe
	ntial voices in the game.️ Learn From the LegendsWe’ve curated an unparalle
	led roster of international talent. Join these icons for deep-dives into t
	he craft:Ivy Mix: Global bar owner and co-founder of Speed Rack.Jeffrey Mo
	rgenthaler: Renowned author and master of modern bar management.Camper Eng
	lish: The world’s leading "cocktail scientist" and expert on spirits physi
	cs.Jim Romdall: Seattle’s industry veteran on sustainability and long-term
	 bar business....plus dozens more global ambassadors and master distillers
	. Three Tracks to MasteryOur curriculum is strategically divided into thre
	e pillars of excellence\, allowing you to customize your education based o
	n your career goals:The Skills Track: Precision meets innovation. These ha
	nds-on labs and technical sessions focus on the "how" behind world-class d
	rinks—covering everything from advanced ice programs and molecular science
	 to creative menu development and speed of service.The Spirits Track: This
	 is for the true student of the glass. Go deep into the technical heritage
	 of global categories like Cognac and Pisco\, explore distillation secrets
	 with master producers\, and refine your palate with curated tastings of r
	are expressions and new releases.The Business Track: Build a career that l
	asts. These sessions tackle the "why" and "how much" of the industry—focus
	ing on bar operations\, sustainable business models\, hospitality leadersh
	ip\, and maintaining physical and mental wellness for a long-term career.️ 
	Secure Your Global AccessThe Summit Class Pass - $45The International Prof
	essional’s Choice Full 3-day access to all educational tracks \\(Skills\, 
	Spirits\, Business\\) at Pacific Place. Includes entry to exclusive indust
	ry lounges and global networking sessions.The Pro-Bundle \\(Summit \\+ Car
	nival of Cocktails\\) - $75The Ultimate Experience | Best Value Maximize y
	our trip to Seattle. This combo deal is for those who want the full educat
	ional foundation plus the high-energy celebration of the Saturday Carnival
	.Full 3-Day Summit Access: Every class\, every speaker\, every track.Satur
	day Carnival Entry: The PNW’s largest spirits tasting event at Pacific Pla
	ce.12 Tasting Tokens: Sample 100\\+ brands and immersive pop-ups.The Bundl
	e Discount: Get the best industry rate by pairing your education and your 
	celebration.\n\nhttps://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/bartender-s-
	circle-summit-2026-seattle-cocktail-week/18061672/2026-04-22T00
URL:https://seatoday.6amcity.com/events/#/details/bartender-s-circle-summit
	-2026-seattle-cocktail-week/18061672/2026-04-22T00
