SUMMARY:Keep Bellevue Beautiful - East Side Cleanup
DTSTAMP:20260413T004130Z
DTSTART:20260425T160000Z
DESCRIPTION:Keep Bellevue Beautiful - East Side Cleanup\n\nEReed\n\nTue\, 0
	3/17/2026 - 13:17\n\nApril 25 2026\n\n9:00 AM - 11:00 AM\n\nAll Day Event\
	n\nOff\n\nEvent Registration\n\nOn\n\nContact\n\nEvan Reed\n\nEmail\n\nere
	ed@bellevuewa.gov\n\nTelephone\n\n425-452-5372\n\nLocation\n\nSouth Bellev
	ue Community Center\, 14509 SE Newport Way\,\n\nDescription\n\nThe City of
	 Bellevue's Keep Bellevue Beautiful program is launching\n\n26 in '26\,\n\
	nan effort aimed at completing\n\n26 Signature Street cleanups\n\nin 2026.
	 The goal is simple: show up consistently\, take care of our streets and s
	upport cleaner\, more welcoming neighborhoods.\n\nDate:\n\nSaturday\, Apri
	l 25\n\nTime:\n\n9-11 a.m.\n\nStart Location:\n\nSouth Bellevue Community 
	Center\n\nFor this special East Side Cleanup\, volunteers will begin at So
	uth Bellevue Community Center before choosing their own cleanup route acro
	ss any of the following neighborhoods:\n\nNortheast Bellevue\n\nCrossroads
	\n\nLake Hills\n\nWest Lake Sammamish\n\nEastgate\n\nSomerset\n\nCougar Mo
	untain/Lakemont\n\nExperience is not required\, and all cleanup supplies w
	ill be provided. Volunteers are welcome to stay for the full two hours or 
	drop in and help for as long as they can. Coffee and water will be availab
	le.\n\nWhen you're done\, simply leave your filled trash bags and gear at 
	the previously agreed upon location within your cleanup neighborhood. A st
	aff member will retrieve everything at the end of the event.\n\nRegister:\
	n\nCleanEastBellevue.EventBrite.com\n\nHide from City Calendar\n\nOff\n\nC
	anceled\n\nOff\n\nLocation\n\nSouth Bellevue Community Center\n\nhttps://s
